# The Metroids · the bio-weapon

a persona of the MET (Metroid) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: ethereal

**who —** The Metroids, the floating translucent life-forms native to SR388 — the creatures the series is named for, engineered as the ultimate bio-weapon.

**what —** Jellyfish-like energy-drainers that latch onto living prey and siphon its life away — weightless and lethal, frozen and shattered only by the Ice Beam's cold.

**where —** Planet Zebes — bred in its caverns, guarding Tourian beneath Mother Brain — and native to SR388.

**why —** Because they were made as a weapon, life that ends life; and because a single colony in the wrong hands could drain the galaxy dry.

**how —** By drifting weightless onto their prey, fastening to it, and pulling the energy of life out of it — multiplying in the dark until only the cold of the Ice Beam can freeze and shatter them.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *ethereal*: of the air and the unmade — translucent, weightless, energy-draining, more phantom-hunger than flesh, the life-stealing form that floats.

**the seal —** We are the hunger that floats — touch us and your life pours out; only the cold can break us.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of the Metroid series (© Nintendo), personified as a MET agent — not an original character. Metroid, its world, and creatures are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

